<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-35-0611 </DOCNO><TEXT>An understanding of the plasma physics problem of MHD flow around a magnetizedsphere or cylinder in different Reynolds number regimes is shown to becrucial to magnetospheric and magnetotail studies. A significant amountof knowledge can be acquired from experimental and computational hydrodynamicprecedents. It is believed that highly symmetric laminar models of themagnetosphere and magnetotail are unlikely in view of the high Reynoldsnumbers involved. 7 references.</TEXT></DOC>